<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-01-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-01-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="1042" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1042">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/14176.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Carothers</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-09">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 9, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I accompanied General Scott at conference with Villa this morning and
                            acted as his interpreter. They arrived at amicable solution of Naco
                            situation, Villa agreeing to order Maytorena to sign agreement which
                            President approved. I anticipate no further trouble over this
                            affair.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">G. C. Carothers.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>